Encouraged by the above results, the AuNPs/Cu,I-CDs nanocomposite can catalyze the oxidation of TBHQ to generate a colored oxidized product, and this colored product was determined by colorimetry. The absorbance value of the detection system at 492 nm increases with the increasing amount of TBHQ, and it is accompanied by a blue shift of the absorption band (Fig. 4
                        a). A linear plot was derived from the collected absorbance values against the TBHQ concentration (red line in Fig. 4b) in the range of 0.35–200 mg/kg, and the regression equation was [TBHQ] = 0.0047Abs + 0.056 (mg/kg) (R2 = 0.9942). The detection limit was 23.45 μg/kg based on the calculation as of the signal-to-noise (S/N) ratio of 3. The practicability of the developed detection system was evaluated through detecting the TBHQ in actual samples including chilli oil and chilli sauce (Table S2). The linear range and detection limit of this method are equal or even better than that of reported methods (Table S3
                        ). From this observation, it can be concluded that the synthesized composite showing a promising detection property to determine the concentration of TBHQ.
